&lt;div class="hero-inner"&gt;
    &lt;div class="hero-title"&gt;Asylum and Migration Policy&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;p class="hero-sub"&gt;Policy-relevant work, reports, and publications on asylum and migration governance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
Next to my academic work, I occasionally contribute to or organise publications and events that inform policy-makers and broader audiences about migration research and current practices. Between 2021 and 2024, I was the National Expert for Germany for the Asylum Information Database. The Database is managed by the European Council on Refugees and Exiles (ECRE) and provides up-to-date information on asylum policy, law, and practice for researchers, advocates, legal practitioners, and the public. Before starting my PhD, I worked as a Research Associate for the European Migration Network, co-authoring studies on various aspects of migration and asylum policy in Germany.

&lt;div class="hero-inner"&gt;
    &lt;div class="hero-title"&gt;Teaching&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;p class="hero-sub"&gt;Courses and supervision on EU policy-making, migration policy, and comparative politics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
I teach classes and supervise BA- and MA-theses on EU policy-making, migration policies, and comparative politics.
